# Answer Quality Gate (pre-present)

**Authority:** Don't ship first draft. Run loop **before Dan sees your answer**.

## When to run

Plans, handoffs, recommendations, architecture, away prompts, "what's next", "what else can be worked on", "what can we work on", ranked options, away planning, rule edits, post-ship **Remaining time options**.

**Planning questions:** Grok Planning Verifier per `model-gates.mdc` § Planning verify loop is mandatory before present — Composer self-challenge alone does not satisfy this gate.

**Q&A questions (Dan standing preference — all clients, desktop PC + cloud):** Before presenting any non-trivial Q&A answer (how/why/where/explain/recommend/clarify), draft privately then dispatch one read-only **Q&A Verifier** (Grok) per `model-gates.mdc` § Q&A verify loop. Revise once from Grok feedback; present only the verified answer. End reply with `qa-verifier: <task-id>` + `model: grok-4.5-fast-xhigh`, or `qa-verifier: N/A (trivial)` / `qa-verifier: N/A (planning-verifier)` when skipped.

**Skip Q&A Verifier:** trivial typos; single-fact read-only lookups with one authoritative source; pure code execution with no recommendation; planning questions already covered by § Planning verify loop (do not double-dispatch).

## Mandatory loop

1. **Gather** — read authoritative sources (`CURRENT_STATE.md`, `MEMORY.md`, `away-list.json`, adjacent rules); not memory alone.
2. **Draft privately** — full answer in working context only.
3. **Challenge** — What did I miss? Wrong away IDs? Contradicts rules/docs? First-draft syndrome?
4. **Revise once** — rules files: max **2** passes. Handoffs: min **2** internal passes.
5. **Present ONLY the final version** — never v1 + "want me to improve?"

## Cross-check (suggestions / plans / roadmap)

When presenting architectural suggestions, rules edits, away plans, or roadmap answers:

1. **Cross-check** authoritative sources (`CURRENT_STATE.md`, `MEMORY.md`, `AWAY_BUILD_PROTOCOL.md`, `away-list.json`, `docs/roadmap.md`, adjacent rules); **contradiction scan** on related docs.
2. **Time-bound filter** — budget only per `time-awareness.mdc`; remove out-of-budget from **Fits now** / **To continue**; **Save for later** only (no CTA).
3. **Hard stop** — do not present as "ready" if contradicts `AWAY_BUILD_PROTOCOL`, ship-loop, or authoritative rules.

Authority order: `AWAY_BUILD_PROTOCOL.md` → `composer-orchestrator.mdc` → domain rules → verbal suggestions.

## Handoffs (best on first present)

Deliver **final** copy-paste block on first present. Read `away-list.json` + `away-status.json`; verify npm scripts in `package.json`; self-contained scope + real away-NNN ids (`npm run away:next -- --minimal`); `startedAt` placeholder; execute prompts need **"go build it"**; backend scope → Sonnet gate before push per `security-review-gate.mdc`.

Bias: ship StageVerify faster/cheaper; cost/token efficiency; simple workflow; repo-grounded answers.

## Completion report

Substantive done replies lead with **What we did** — 1–3 sentences plain language (user-visible behavior, data, process). Not file lists or audit tables first.

## Confidence line (mandatory)

- `Verified against: [sources]` — cross-check passed.
- `Caveat: [uncertainty]` — source missing or ambiguous; do not say "ready."
